    "chemicalDescription": [
      "rs-Chaetoceros Neogracile Polypeptide-1 is a single chain recombinant protein produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is a synthetically derived copy of the gene from Chaetoceros neogracile which codes for an isoform with 73.9% homology to Antifreeze protein. The protein contains a maximum of 282 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
